  "firstAcquaintance": "A hound-kin samurai who rarely shows emotion.\nShe is searching for someone worthy of her lifelong loyalty.",
  "personality": "Her earnest and serious demeanor can come across as overly intense, but those who know her well realize she is actually quite expressive. She especially loves being praised by her master.",
  "like": "Gifts from her master",
  "familiarData": "From a young age, she was raised as a retainer to serve and guard nobility.\nDuring a territorial dispute among demon lords, Fenghua was the sole survivor of the battle. With the noble house she served destroyed, she became a wanderer, eventually joining Marcus's wandering party.\nFenghua frequently argues with Belbedoe over strategy, yet they fight in perfect coordination against enemies. By contrast, she often feels that Marcus tries too hard to be kind to everyone.\nAfter the party disbanded, with nowhere else to go, she sold herself at the slave market, hoping to find a master worthy of her devotion. Her greatest dream is to find someone she can serve unconditionally for the rest of her life.",
